9 (a) Except as provided in subsections (b), (e), [and] (f), AND (G) of this section,
10 each public school under the jurisdiction of a county board:
11 (1) (i) Shall be open for pupil attendance for at least 180 actual school
12 days and a minimum of 1,080 school hours during a 10–month period in each school year;
13 or
14 (ii) If normal school attendance is prevented because of conditions
15 described in subsection (b) of this section, shall be open for at least 1,080 hours during a
16 10–month period;
17 (2) Shall be open for pupil attendance a minimum of 3 hours during each
18 school day; and
19 (3) May not be open on Saturdays, Sundays, or holidays in order to meet
20 the 180–day or 1,080–hour requirement of this subsection.
21 (b) (1) If a county board submits a written application to the State Board that
22 describes a demonstrated effort by the county board to comply with subsection (a) of this
23 section, the State Board may permit:
24 (i) The following adjustments:
25 1. An increase in the length of the school year; or
26 2. A decrease in the length of the school year;
27 (ii) Exceptions from the requirement that the school year be
28 completed within a 10–month period;
29 (iii) Adjustments in the length of the school day; and
30 (iv) Schools to be open on holidays.

